<section
  class="hc-stages-odor"
  style="
    --hc-so-pt-mobile: {{ section.settings.padding_top_mobile }}px;
    --hc-so-pb-mobile: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom_mobile }}px;
    --hc-so-pt-desktop: {{ section.settings.padding_top_desktop }}px;
    --hc-so-pb-desktop: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom_desktop }}px;
  "
>
  <div class="hc-stages-odor__container">

    <div class="hc-stages-odor__header">
      {%- if section.settings.eyebrow != blank -%}
        <span class="hc-stages-odor__eyebrow">{{ section.settings.eyebrow }}</span>
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- if section.settings.heading != blank -%}
        <h2 class="hc-stages-odor__heading">{{ section.settings.heading }}</h2>
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- if section.settings.subtext != blank -%}
        <p class="hc-stages-odor__subtext">{{ section.settings.subtext }}</p>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    {%- if section.blocks.size > 0 -%}
      <div class="hc-stages-odor__grid">
        {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
          {%- if block.type == 'stage' -%}
            <article
              class="hc-stages-odor__stage hc-stages-odor__stage--{{ block.settings.theme }}"
              {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
            >
              {%- if block.settings.step_number != blank -%}
                <span class="hc-stages-odor__stage-num" aria-hidden="true">{{ block.settings.step_number }}</span>
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if block.settings.title != blank -%}
                <h3 class="hc-stages-odor__stage-title">{{ block.settings.title }}</h3>
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if block.settings.body != blank -%}
                <div class="hc-stages-odor__stage-body">{{ block.settings.body }}</div>
              {%- endif -%}
            </article>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hc-stages-odor {
    background-color: #fff;
    padding-top: var(--hc-so-pt-mobile);
    padding-bottom: var(--hc-so-pb-mobile);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    padding-right: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hc-stages-odor {
      padding-left: 3rem;
      padding-right: 3rem;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .hc-stages-odor {
      padding-top: var(--hc-so-pt-desktop);
      padding-bottom: var(--hc-so-pb-desktop);
    }
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__container {
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__eyebrow {
    display: block;
    color: #B45309;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__heading {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #050505;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hc-stages-odor__heading {
      font-size: 3.75rem;
    }
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__subtext {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hc-stages-odor__grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage {
    padding: 2.5rem;
    border-radius: 1.5rem;
    border-width: 1px;
    border-style: solid;
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--light {
    background-color: #f9fafb;
    border-color: #f3f4f6;
    color: #000;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--light:hover {
    border-color: rgba(180, 83, 9, 0.3);
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--dark {
    background-color: #000;
    border-color: #1f2937;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--dark:hover {
    border-color: #B45309;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage-num {
    display: block;
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #B45309;
    opacity: 0.2;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--light .hc-stages-odor__stage-title {
    color: #050505;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--dark .hc-stages-odor__stage-title {
    color: #fff;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage-body {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--light .hc-stages-odor__stage-body {
    color: #4b5563;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage--dark .hc-stages-odor__stage-body {
    color: #9ca3af;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage-body p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .hc-stages-odor__stage-body strong {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: inherit;
  }
</style>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "HC Odor Stages",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "hc-stages-odor-section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Header"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "The Methodology"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "3 Stages of Odor Control"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "subtext",
      "label": "Subtext",
      "default": "We don't just react to odor; we preempt it. Our fabrics are engineered to perform across three critical stages of the biological scent cycle."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Spacing — Mobile"
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top_mobile",
      "label": "Padding Top (Mobile)",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 64
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom_mobile",
      "label": "Padding Bottom (Mobile)",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 64
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Spacing — Desktop"
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top_desktop",
      "label": "Padding Top (Desktop)",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 128
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom_desktop",
      "label": "Padding Bottom (Desktop)",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 128
    }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "stage",
      "name": "Stage",
      "settings": [
        {
          "type": "select",
          "id": "theme",
          "label": "Card style",
          "options": [
            { "value": "light", "label": "Light (gray background)" },
            { "value": "dark", "label": "Dark (black background)" }
          ],
          "default": "light"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "step_number",
          "label": "Step number",
          "default": "01"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "title",
          "label": "Title",
          "default": "Prevention"
        },
        {
          "type": "richtext",
          "id": "body",
          "label": "Body",
          "default": "<p>The best way to handle odor-causing bacteria is to not have it in the first place. The most effective way of prevention is moisture management. The more you can prevent the bacteria from getting to your sweat, the better. We used one of the most powerful fibers as the core of our clothing so few other clothing prevents odor as effectively as HercLeón.</p><p>This is why plastic fibers (polyester, nylon, acrylic, etc.) are the worst because it's like wearing a plastic bag, they act like a greenhouse, trapping heat and forcing you to sweat more. It's literally the worst thing you can wear if you want to smell good. That's why within an hour of wearing polyester or nylon clothing they usually start to stink.</p><p>Now, of course, if you wear things like cotton, viscose, silk, linen and animal hair (aka wool), your clothes will be able to handle the moisture better which will help it stay cleaner longer.</p>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "HC Odor Stages",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "stage",
          "settings": {
            "theme": "light",
            "step_number": "01",
            "title": "Prevention",
            "body": "<p>The best way to handle odor-causing bacteria is to not have it in the first place. The most effective way of prevention is moisture management. The more you can prevent the bacteria from getting to your sweat, the better. We used one of the most powerful fibers as the core of our clothing so few other clothing prevents odor as effectively as HercLeón.</p><p>This is why plastic fibers (polyester, nylon, acrylic, etc.) are the worst because it's like wearing a plastic bag, they act like a greenhouse, trapping heat and forcing you to sweat more. It's literally the worst thing you can wear if you want to smell good. That's why within an hour of wearing polyester or nylon clothing they usually start to stink.</p><p>Now, of course, if you wear things like cotton, viscose, silk, linen and animal hair (aka wool), your clothes will be able to handle the moisture better which will help it stay cleaner longer.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "stage",
          "settings": {
            "theme": "dark",
            "step_number": "02",
            "title": "Neutralization",
            "body": "<p>Very few fibers actually perform this crucial step. While natural fibers manage moisture, they don't actively fight the bacteria that inevitably arrive. This is why neutralization is an essential part of handling and preventing odor.</p><p>This is where our proprietary matrix comes in. We embed a permanent blend of minerals and metals that actively pierce bacterial cell walls and disrupt their DNA. We don't just slow them down; we neutralize the odor-causing bacteria on contact, preventing the off-gassing process entirely. There's no clothing on earth that we're aware of that comes close to ours in this aspect. Even military grade is beneath us at this point.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "stage",
          "settings": {
            "theme": "light",
            "step_number": "03",
            "title": "Absorption & Adsorption",
            "body": "<p>Even with perfect prevention and neutralization, complex hormonal odors and environmental smells can still occur.</p><p>To combat this, we utilize highly porous materials (like volcanic ash and coconut charcoal) that act as microscopic sponges. Through both absorption and <strong>adsorption</strong>, they catch and trap any extra odor molecules that might happen naturally, locking them deep inside the fiber matrix so it helps keep your clothing smelling as good as possible. Most companies never solve for this but we also excel in this category as well.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
